data.Name: METAL PLATING
data.Subtitle: Crafted Technology Component
data.Description:
A lightweight metal product, heavily used in the manufacture of <TECHNOLOGY>starship parts<> and <TECHNOLOGY>deployable technology<>. A mainstay of the construction industries of all known primary species.

Crafted from <EARTH>Ferrite Dust<>.

data.Name: CARBON NANOTUBES
data.Subtitle: Crafted Technology Component
data.Description:
Metres and metres of high capacity <FUEL>carbon nanotubes<>.

Their high tensile strength and mild conductivity make these a key component in many <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

data.Name: HERMETIC SEAL
data.Subtitle: Crafted Technology Component
data.Description:
A high-performance <FUEL>carbon seal<>, able to withstand both the harsh interstellar environment and the rigours of intensive, high-energy industrial use.

User is advised to regularly check seal integrity after installation.

data.Name: MICROPROCESSOR
data.Subtitle: Crafted Technology Component
data.Description:
A compact, <TECHNOLOGY>low-heat microchip<>. Assembled from processed <STELLAR>Chromatic Metal<>, created from one of several specialised terrain metals.

Used in the creation of a wide range of <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

data.Name: OXYGEN CAPSULE
data.Subtitle: Portable Life Support Power
data.Description:
Stablised and secure <FUEL>life support<> filtration gas.

Easily assembled from <FUEL>Oxygen<> and <EARTH>Ferrite Dust<>. Offers an efficient method for long-term life support power.

data.Name: LIFE SUPPORT GEL
data.Subtitle: Portable Life Support Power
data.Description:
Emergency <FUEL>life support fuel<>.

Synthesised from <TECHNOLOGY>rocket fuel crystals<> and <FUEL>carbon<>, this gel offers a temporary boost to life support systems. Long-term impact on user's lungs is currently unknown.

data.Name: ION BATTERY
data.Subtitle: Portable Energy Storage
data.Description:
Convenient and optimised power storage unit. Used in a wide variety of <COMMODITY>defensive<> and <COMMODITY>hazard protection<> systems.
 
Constructed by fusing <EARTH>Ferrite Dust<> with underground <TECHNOLOGY>Cobalt<>. Frequently found ready-made in cylindrical metal containers.

data.Name: ADVANCED ION BATTERY
data.Subtitle: Portable Energy Storage
data.Description:
Powerful energy storage unit. Used in a wide variety of <COMMODITY>defensive<> and <COMMODITY>hazard protection<> systems.

Constructed from <TECHNOLOGY>Ionised Cobalt<> and <EARTH>Pure Ferrite<>, and occasionally found in cylindrical metal containers.

data.Name: DI-HYDROGEN JELLY
data.Subtitle: Portable Life Support Power
data.Description:
A faintly-glowing jelly. Its gentle light and soft wobble belie the fact that this sticky gel is both highly toxic and highly flammable. Skin contact is to be avoided at all costs.

Synthesised from <TECHNOLOGY>Di-hydrogen<>.

data.Name: STARSHIP LAUNCH FUEL
data.Subtitle: Stabilised Di-hydrogen Fuel
data.Description:
Highly reactive solid-state fuel, required to fuel <TECHNOLOGY>Starship Launch Thrusters<>.

Created from crystallised <TECHNOLOGY>Di-hydrogen<>, found in blue deposits on all worlds.

data.Name: UNSTABLE PLASMA
data.Subtitle: Plasma Launcher Recharge
data.Description:
Densely-packed fuel capsule for use in the <TECHNOLOGY>Plasma Launcher<>.
 
Contained highly-pressurised electro-thermal energy for use in land disruption grenade technology.

data.Name: PROJECTILE AMMUNITION
data.Subtitle: Universal Ammo Module
data.Description:
Advanced munition fragments, constructed to fit Universal Multi-Tool Standard 07/FF1.

Easily inserted into the <TECHNOLOGY>Boltcaster<>, <TECHNOLOGY>Pulse Spitter<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Scatter Blaster<> via the Multi-Tool clip reloading system.

data.Name: ANTIMATTER HOUSING
data.Subtitle: Crafted Technology Component
data.Description:
Secure antimatter containment device, required before <FUEL>Antimatter<> can be safely secured as <FUEL>Warp Cells<>.

Rebound <FUEL>Oxygen<> forms a protective gas pocket, preventing the antimatter from reacting with the surrounding casing.

data.Name: ANTIMATTER
data.Subtitle: Crafted Technology Component
data.Description:
Contained negative matter and baryogenesis antiparticles.
 
The vast energy potential of antimatter makes it highly valuable. 95% of existing antimatter consumption is in the powering of <TECHNOLOGY>starship hyperdrives<>.

<FUEL>WARNING<>: uncontained usage is not recommended.

data.Name: WARP CELL
data.Subtitle: Hyperdrive Charging Unit
data.Description:
This <FUEL>antimatter-based fuel<> is one of the few power sources capable of meeting the incredible energy requirements of a <TECHNOLOGY>starship hyperdrive<>.

Secured within a robust housing, the cell is guarenteed paradox-free during FTL travel.

data.Name: OXYGEN FILTER
data.Subtitle: Crafted Technology Component
data.Description:
A specialist technology component.

This small device can rapidly change the gaseous environment within a device, handling conditions from total vacuum to pure oxygen atmospheres.

data.Name: SALT REFRACTOR
data.Subtitle: Crafted Technology Component
data.Description:
A specialist technology component, vital to the complex internals of modern laser systems. 

This light-scattering device takes advantage of the unique optical properties of stabilised and polished salt, to both slow and refract passing photons.

data.Name: COBALT MIRROR
data.Subtitle: Crafted Technology Component
data.Description:
A specialist optical component.

Employing a polished cobalt surface, this mirror is able to selectively filter different wavelengths of light, changing its reflective pattern based on nearby magnetic fields.

data.Name: SODIUM DIODE
data.Subtitle: Crafted Technology Component
data.Description:
An advanced circuit component.

The refined sodium electrode within its vacuum tube gives this diode specialist surge-protection capabilities.

data.Name: QUAD SERVO
data.Subtitle: Anomalous Material
data.Description: A highly sprung motor arm salvaged from inside of a Sentinel patrol unit. It occasionally twitches, as if experiencing the echo of combat.

data.Name: WALKER BRAIN
data.Subtitle: Anomalous Material
data.Description:
Shifting nanite clusters sewn together with a pugneum filament, this circuit is painfully hot to the touch.

A sinister purple light leaks from deep within its wiring, changing in intensity as it watches its holder.

data.Name: TECHNOLOGY MODULE
data.Subtitle: Technology Wiring Platform
data.Description:
A prefabricated circuit board, designed for flexible use in a large range of <TECHNOLOGY>technology components<>.

The module features an integrated nanite processor, allowing it to be quickly configured for a wide variety of uses.

data.Name: CARBON CRYSTAL
data.Subtitle: Concentrated Carbon Deposit
data.Description:
Hyper-compressed <FUEL>carbon<>, this substance's dense nanostructure makes it highly valuable as both an energy source and a technology component.

Synthesised from <FUEL>Condensed Carbon<>.

data.Name: RARE METAL ELEMENT
data.Subtitle: Concentrated Metal Deposit
data.Description:
A highly-prized metal product, this rare element is used in the manufacture of several advanced technologies.

Metal is highly reactive and quickly bonds to exposed skin. User is advised to handle with extreme caution.

Synthesised from <EARTH>Magnetised Ferrite<>.

data.Name: TETRACOBALT
data.Subtitle: Concentrated Cobalt Deposit
data.Description:
A novel molecular form of <TECHNOLOGY>Cobalt<>, requiring very high energy levels to create. Natural occurrence is extremely rare.

Synthesised from <TECHNOLOGY>Ionised Cobalt<>.

data.Name: CHLORIDE LATTICE
data.Subtitle: Concentrated Chlorine Deposit
data.Description:
A tightly-bonded form of Chlorine. Rigidly-packed molecules offer unrivalled conductivity. Not known to form spontaneously: creation requires highly-focused energy inputs.

Synthesised from <CATALYST>Chlorine<>.

data.Name: DESTABLISED SODIUM
data.Subtitle: Concentrated Sodium Deposit
data.Description:
Sodium is typically highly stable, but certain configurations retain the reactivity of its component ions. User is advised to wear <TECHNOLOGY>Hazardous Material Gauntlets<> before handling.

Synthesised from <TRADEABLE>Sodium<>.

data.Name: SUPEROXIDE CRYSTAL
data.Subtitle: Concentrated Oxygen Deposit
data.Description:
A para-magnetic form of Oxygen, this rare substance has much to offer in the production of <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>. Requires conversion prior to input into Life Support systems. Direct inhalation is NOT recommended.

Synthesised from <FUEL>Oxygen<>.

data.Name: SAC VENOM
data.Subtitle: Trade commodity
data.Description:
Stabilised poison sample initially produced by aquatic urchin creatures.

A rare and expensive item on the Galactic Trade Network.

data.Name: GRAVITINO BALL
data.Subtitle: Trade commodity
data.Description:
Supersymmetric particle cluster.

Extremely rare and valuable. A product of divergent super-gravitational forces.

data.Name: ALBUMEN PEARL
data.Subtitle: Trade commodity
data.Description:
Gemstone formed over the course of centuries within the egg of a super-incubatory species.

Extremely rare.

data.Name: VORTEX CUBE
data.Subtitle: Trade commodity
data.Description:
Dense metal objects that, long ago, materialised within subterranean networks throughout the Galaxy.

Extremely rare, and of high value.

data.Name: ARONIUM
data.Subtitle: Alloy Metal
data.Description:
A lightweight and highly malleable alloy. Crafted from <EARTH>Paraffinium<> and <EARTH>Chlorine<>.

In high demand on the Galactic Trade Network due to its utility in the construction of planetside outposts and facilities.

data.Name: DIRTY BRONZE
data.Subtitle: Alloy Metal
data.Description:
A popular metal alloy with a wide variety of uses. 'Dirty Bronze' has shed its scientific name in favour of the popular term for its colour.

Crafted from <EARTH>Pure Ferrite<> and <EARTH>Pyrite<>.

data.Name: HEROX
data.Subtitle: Alloy Metal
data.Description:
Combined neutral alloy with uses that range from pharmacology all the way to heavy industry. Crafted from <EARTH>Chlorine<> and <EARTH>Ammonia<>.

Forms the backbone of galactic alloy trading.

data.Name: LEMMIUM
data.Subtitle: Alloy Metal
data.Description:
Pure Ferrite alloy. Crafted from <EARTH>Pure Ferrite<> and <EARTH>Uranium<>.

Used extensively in starship freighter construction due to its sheer strength. A hardcore material popular on the Galactic Trade Network.

data.Name: MAGNO-GOLD
data.Subtitle: Alloy Metal
data.Description:
Highly prized and lustrous alloy. Popular with traders of all known primary galactic races. Crafted from <EARTH>Ionised Cobalt<> and <EARTH>Phosphorus<>.

Easily recognisable by its bright red glow and strong magnetic field.

data.Name: GRANTINE
data.Subtitle: Alloy Metal
data.Description:
Soft workable alloy favoured by artisans throughout the known galaxy. Crafted from <EARTH>Ionised Cobalt<> and <EARTH>Dioxite<>.

A popular trading good, with many galactic shipping paths devoted to its sale and transport.

data.Name: GEODESITE
data.Subtitle: Enriched Alloy Metal
data.Description:
Advanced and durable alloy primarily used in starship hull construction and deep-space exploration drone technology.

Crafted from <SPECIAL>Herox<>, <SPECIAL>Dirty Bronze<> and <SPECIAL>Lemmium<>.

data.Name: IRIDESITE
data.Subtitle: Enriched Alloy Metal
data.Description:
Advanced light metal alloy traded throughout the galactic Outer Edge. Often used in the interiors of trading shuttles to reduce weight as they ascend from planets with high gravitational fields.

Crafted from <SPECIAL>Aronium<>, <SPECIAL>Magno-Gold<> and <SPECIAL>Grantine<>.

data.Name: ANCIENT KEY
data.Subtitle: Timeless Artifact
data.Description: A key of some weight, this aged piece of wrought iron must belong in a nearby lock...

data.Name: NAVIGATION DATA
data.Subtitle: Encrypted Navigation Data
data.Description:
Encoded navigation data for input into a <TECHNOLOGY>Signal Booster<>.

When properly decrypted, will reveal the location of a planetary <COMMODITY>point of interest<> or <FUEL>building<>.

data.Name: DROP POD COORDINATE DATA
data.Subtitle: Encrypted Navigation Data
data.Description:
Encoded navigation data for input into a <TECHNOLOGY>Signal Booster<>.

When properly decrypted, will reveal the location of a <TECHNOLOGY>Drop Pod<> containing <SPECIAL>Exosuit Upgrades<>.

data.Name: ATLASPASS v1
data.Subtitle: Access Card
data.Description:
Security and permissions pass granted to specific travellers by many primary galactic species.

Provides access to low level restricted areas and outpost systems.

data.Name: ATLASPASS v2
data.Subtitle: Access Card
data.Description:
Security and permissions pass granted to specific travellers by many primary galactic species.
 
Provides access to mid-tier restricted areas and outpost systems.

data.Name: ATLASPASS v3
data.Subtitle: Access Card
data.Description:
Security and permissions pass granted to specific travellers by many primary galactic species.
 
Provides access to high level restricted areas and outpost systems.

data.Name: DEFENCE CHIT
data.Subtitle: System Authority Payment Substitute
data.Description: A token, entitling the bearer to support from the system authorities in dealing with pirate attacks.

data.Name: MIND ARC
data.Subtitle: Advanced Crafted Product
data.Description: A strange piece of technology, a gift from beyond the stars. It shimmers in way that suggests it is not fully in this world.

data.Name: SALVAGED TECHNOLOGY
data.Subtitle: Damaged Data Unit
data.Description:
An old data bank, the last remains of some alien technology.

Useless in its current form, a <TECHNOLOGY>Blueprint Analyser<> will reveal any useful technology contained within.

data.Name: FRIGATE FUEL (50 TONNES)
data.Subtitle: Stabilised Di-hydrogen Fuel
data.Description:
A small barrel of frigate fuel.

This viscous gel is highly toxic to the touch. A refined fuel, it powers the interstellar engines of large trading ships.

data.Name: FRIGATE FUEL (100 TONNES)
data.Subtitle: Stabilised Di-hydrogen Fuel
data.Description:
A large barrel of frigate fuel.

This viscous gel is highly toxic to the touch. A refined fuel, it powers the interstellar engines of large trading ships.

data.Name: FRIGATE FUEL (200 TONNES)
data.Subtitle: Stabilised Di-hydrogen Fuel
data.Description:
A huge barrel of frigate fuel.

This viscous gel is highly toxic to the touch. A refined fuel, it powers the interstellar engines of large trading ships.

data.Name: MIND CONTROL DEVICE
data.Subtitle: Consumable Frigate Upgrade
data.Description:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

The mind control device plugs into the ship's trading and communications systems, allowing the Fleet Commander to gain the upper hand in any negotiation.

data.Name: HOLOGRAPHIC ANALYSER
data.Subtitle: Consumable Frigate Upgrade
data.Description:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

This powerful analytic computer overclocks the existing fleet systems, allowing for faster-than-light calculations. Heat is a problem, and the chips do not last long.

data.Name: MINERAL COMPRESSOR
data.Subtitle: Consumable Frigate Upgrade
data.Description:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

The mineral compressor allows fleet mining crews to liquidise the substances they extract, for both faster processing and easier transportation.

data.Name: EXPLOSIVE DRONES
data.Subtitle: Consumable Frigate Upgrade
data.Description:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

This pack of autonomous explosives have been programmed to launch from the fleet and pilot themselves directly towards hostile vessels. Extremely dangerous.

data.Name: FUEL OXIDISER
data.Subtitle: Consumable Frigate Upgrade
data.Description:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

This powerful fuel upgrade overloads frigate engines, allowing for faster-than-usual travel.

data.Name: GEK RELIC
data.Subtitle: Medium value curiosity
data.Description:
A metal statuette of a creature with a coin placed in its beak.
 
Popular with many traders who see it as an emblem of fair commerce and peace.

data.Name: GEKNIP
data.Subtitle: Trade commodity
data.Description:
Edible product much beloved by the Gek.
 
Allows beaked traders to release delightfully scented packets of gas for a prolonged period of time.
 
GekNip gas packets are considered an art form, and the truest representation of the Gek soul.

data.Name: NIPNIP BUDS
data.Subtitle: Medicinal Substance
data.Description: A pungent bud harvested from the NipNip plant, often used to produce Gek Nip.

data.Name: VY'KEEN EFFIGY
data.Subtitle: Medium value curiosity
data.Description:
A small wooden icon carved into the shape of a Sentinel drone.
 
Used by warriors to enter a temporary trance-like state that eliminates their kind's need for sleep.

data.Name: VY'KEEN DAGGER
data.Subtitle: Trade commodity
data.Description: Largely ceremonial weapon. A vital part of Vy'keen tradition and culture.

data.Name: KORVAX CASING
data.Subtitle: High value curiosity
data.Description:
The metallic shell of a disconnected electronic lifeform that was too distant from its kind to be refreshed with a new entity.
 
Highly prized by all species, not least its own.

data.Name: KORVAX CONVERGENCE CUBE
data.Subtitle: Trade commodity
data.Description: Device used by the Korvax for the storage of historical and cultural information.

data.Name: ACID
data.Subtitle: Advanced Agricultural Product
data.Description:
Dilute acid for high current generation in diverse power cells.

Crafted from <SPECIAL>Mordite<> and <TRADEABLE>Fungal Mould<>.

data.Name: LUBRICANT
data.Subtitle: Advanced Agricultural Product
data.Description:
A synthetic lubricant that reduces wear and prolongs the lifespan of technologies with moving parts.

Crafted from <FUEL>Coprite<> and <TRADEABLE>Gamma Root<>.

data.Name: GLASS
data.Subtitle: Advanced Agricultural Product
data.Description:
Shatter-proof, scratch-resistant glass with a self-cleaning, UV-cured coating, for general construction use.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Frost Crystals<>.

data.Name: HEAT CAPACITOR
data.Subtitle: Advanced Agricultural Product
data.Description:
A thermal regulator produced from refined organic material. It is unique it its ability to produce, dissipate and distribute heat as required.

Crafted from <SPECIAL>Solanium<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Frost Crystals<>.

data.Name: POLY FIBRE
data.Subtitle: Advanced Agricultural Product
data.Description:
A connective fibre for electronics, made from an advanced synthetic polymer and capable of serving as a conduit for power and data.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Cactus Flesh<> and <TRADEABLE>Star Bulbs<>.

data.Name: UNSTABLE GEL
data.Subtitle: Advanced Agricultural Product
data.Description:
A highly reactive gel, this substance is both energy-rich and dangerous to touch.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Cactus Flesh<>.

data.Name: LIQUID EXPLOSIVE
data.Subtitle: Advanced Agricultural Product
data.Description:
A general purpose high explosive, offered in liquid form for convenience of transport and deployment. Do not drink.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Acid<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Unstable Gel<>.

data.Name: LIVING GLASS
data.Subtitle: Advanced Agricultural Product
data.Description:
An advanced building material, this glass has been imbued with organic compounds that allow it to react to the environment. Microbes within the glass filter harmful light of all wavelengths and balance the atmosphere as required.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Lubricant<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Glass<>.

data.Name: CIRCUIT BOARD
data.Subtitle: Advanced Agricultural Product
data.Description:
Stackable, semi-flexible circuit board made from a highly durable synthetic polymer.

Crafted from <COMMODITY>Heat Capacitors<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Poly Fibre<>.

data.Name: THERMIC CONDENSATE
data.Subtitle: Enhanced Gas Product
data.Description:
A refined product, holding the energy potential of heated atmospheric gas in a stable state until required.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Sulphurine<> and <FUEL>Condensed Carbon<>.

data.Name: ENRICHED CARBON
data.Subtitle: Enhanced Gas Product
data.Description:
A refined product, taking ordinary carbon and boosting it with radioactive energy.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Radon<> and <FUEL>Condensed Carbon<>.

data.Name: NITROGEN SALT
data.Subtitle: Enhanced Gas Product
data.Description:
A refined product, this is a powerful organic fertiliser in an easily distributed form.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Nitrogen<> and <FUEL>Condensed Carbon<>.

data.Name: ORGANIC CATALYST
data.Subtitle: Manufactured Gas Product
data.Description:
A catalytic material used in the creation of many organic fertilisers.

Crafted from <FUEL>Thermic Condensate<> and <FUEL>Enriched Carbon<>.

data.Name: SEMICONDUCTOR
data.Subtitle: Manufactured Gas Product
data.Description:
An advanced material useful in many electronic devices, with its own in-built temperature regulator.

Crafted from <FUEL>Thermic Condensate<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Nitrogen Salt<>.

data.Name: HOT ICE
data.Subtitle: Manufactured Gas Product
data.Description:
A paradoxical material, made less mysterious by its relative ease of manufacture.

Crafted from <FUEL>Enriched Carbon<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Nitrogen Salt<>.

data.Name: FUSION ACCELERANT
data.Subtitle: Manufactured Gas Product
data.Description:
An advanced fuel source, made from a perfect blend of high potential energy organic materials.

Crafted from <FUEL>Organic Catalyst<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Nitrogen Salt<>.

data.Name: SUPERCONDUCTOR
data.Subtitle: Manufactured Gas Product
data.Description:
An advanced conductive material, the superconductor further enriches the field-warping power of the Semiconductor.

Crafted from <FUEL>Enriched Carbon<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Semiconductors<>.

data.Name: CRYO-PUMP
data.Subtitle: Manufactured Gas Product
data.Description:
An advanced, self-regulating hybrid material, the Cryo-Pump distributes heat across itself with near perfect efficiency, making it vital in the creation of thermal regulators.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Hot Ice<> and <FUEL>Thermic Condensate<>

data.Name: PORTABLE REACTOR
data.Subtitle: Advanced Crafted Product
data.Description:
A miniature self-controlled nuclear reactor. Generates sub-stellar levels of energy in a hassle-free, widely compatible fuel module.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Liquid Explosives<> and <FUEL>Fusion Accelerant<>.

data.Name: QUANTUM PROCESSOR
data.Subtitle: Advanced Crafted Product
data.Description:
A highly advanced computational device, essential for the complex calculations involved in warp travel.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Circuit Boards<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Superconductors<>.

data.Name: CRYOGENIC CHAMBER
data.Subtitle: Advanced Crafted Product
data.Description:
A low temperature chamber, designed to prevent the natural decay of organic matter.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Living Glass<> and a <TECHNOLOGY>Cryo-Pump<>.

data.Name: FUSION IGNITOR
data.Subtitle: Highly Refined Technology
data.Description:
A highly advanced piece of technology for use in the next generation of power plants. Producing a fusion core requires both intricate scientific skills and complex industrial processes.

Crafted from <FUEL>Portable Reactor<>, <TECHNOLOGY>Quantum Processors<> and <SPECIAL>Geodesite<>.

data.Name: STASIS DEVICE
data.Subtitle: Highly Refined Technology
data.Description:
A device specifically crafted to keep lifeforms alive for thousands of years longer than their natural lifespan. Such a device requires great skill to manufacture, as not only is it technically complex, but the consequences for a user in the event of malfunction would be disastrous.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Quantum Processors<>, <TECHNOLOGY>Cryogenic Chambers<>, and <SPECIAL>Iridesite<>.

data.Name: CARBON NANOTUBES
data.Subtitle: Advanced Construction Materials
data.Description:
A packed crate of carbon nanotubes.

These tiny but incredibly strong tubes are required in the construction of tiny but incredibly strong <SPECIAL>scientific components<>.

data.Name: SELF-REPAIRING HERIDIUM
data.Subtitle: Advanced Construction Materials
data.Description:
A hopper of self-repairing Heridium. It looks fresh.

Used in the creation of <SPECIAL>scientific components<>. Self-repairing heridium is particularly useful for deployment in remote facilities, where maintenance opportunities may be limited or deadly.

data.Name: OPTICAL SOLVENT
data.Subtitle: Advanced Construction Materials
data.Description:
Several bottles of optical solvent.

The liquid in these bottles is used to wash away surplus light that may otherwise cause decay in <SPECIAL>scientific components<>.

data.Name: FIVE DIMENSIONAL TORUS
data.Subtitle: Advanced Construction Materials
data.Description:
A specially manufactured container of 5D tori.

Highly specific materials are required to construct shapes in extra dimensions. These tori are used to contain the strong fields generated in the manufacture of <SPECIAL>scientific components<>.

data.Name: SUPERCONDUCTING FIBRE
data.Subtitle: Advanced Construction Materials
data.Description:
A densely layered package of superconducting fibres.

Powerful, flexible, and water-resistant; the controlled magnetic weave of these fibres is vital in the creation of many <SPECIAL>scientific components<>.

data.Name: DECRYPTED USER DATA
data.Subtitle: Trade Commodity
data.Description:
A crate packed with hard drives, each of which contain vast amounts of decrypted user data.

Individually of low value, taken together these repositories can be processed and scanned for valuable data. This processing occurs in systems with <SPECIAL>advanced material<> economies.

data.Name: STAR SILK
data.Subtitle: Trade Commodity
data.Description:
Several spools of star silk.

Star silk is woven on enormous solar looms in orbit around trading planets. Cosmic ray impact triggers the pattern of the weave, which can then be used in <SPECIAL>advanced material<> processing.

data.Name: COMET DROPLETS
data.Subtitle: Trade Commodity
data.Description:
Several canisters of comet droplets.

An elaborate trading name for chunks of meteorite, these rocks are nonetheless extremely valuable to the <SPECIAL>advanced material<> economies that can process them.

data.Name: ION SPHERE
data.Subtitle: Trade Commodity
data.Description:
A packed crate of ion spheres.

These delicate glass spheres house a small-scale replica of the upper atmosphere. Sparkly and hypnotic to look at, these baubles are also of importance in the manufacture of <SPECIAL>advanced material<> alloys.

data.Name: TELEPORT COORDINATORS
data.Subtitle: Trade Commodity
data.Description:
A bundle of precisely calibrated teleport coordinators.

These pin-prick sized circuits are vital to the delicate process of inserting reinforcing material into <SPECIAL>advanced alloys<>. They can also aid long-distance sales efforts.

data.Name: ENORMOUS METAL COG
data.Subtitle: Industrial Components
data.Description:
Several huge cogs.

Sturdy, well-made metal gears. While not advanced technology themselves, they're a vital component in countless pieces of <SPECIAL>high-tech<> machinery all over the galaxy.

data.Name: NON-STICK PISTON
data.Subtitle: Industrial Components
data.Description:
Wrapped and greased pistons, ready for shipping.

<SPECIAL>High-tech<> components frequently require rapidly moving parts, or high-endurance motors. Without specially coated pistons, the failure rate of such parts would be significantly higher.

data.Name: SIX-PRONGED MESH DECOUPLER
data.Subtitle: Industrial Components
data.Description:
A crate of mesh decouplers.

The creation of <SPECIAL>high-tech<> components often involves accidental mesh-coupling. These decouplers are particularly powerful, being able to deploy six prongs simultaneously.

data.Name: HOLOGRAPHIC CRANKSHAFT
data.Subtitle: Industrial Components
data.Description:
Packed and separated data containers for holographic crankshafts.

Real crankshafts are frequently too large, noisy or hard-to-maintain for use in delicate machines. When faced with such a situation, <SPECIAL>high-tech<> manufacturers turn to these holographic substitutes.

data.Name: HIGH CAPACITY VECTOR COMPRESSOR
data.Subtitle: Industrial Components
data.Description:
A large crate of vector compressors.

The creation of interstellar drives often requires dimensions to be condensed and then re-rendered. Such <SPECIAL>high-tech<> component manufacture would not be possible without industrial-grade compressors such as these.

data.Name: SPARK CANISTER
data.Subtitle: Tradable Energy Source
data.Description:
A crate packed with spark canisters.

Many industrial and <SPECIAL>mining<> processes have considerable power demands. A counterpart to the slow release of a battery, spark canisters are able to meet these demands instantaneously.

data.Name: INDUSTRIAL-GRADE BATTERY
data.Subtitle: Tradable Energy Source
data.Description:
A packet of well-isolated industrial batteries.

Heavy-duty batteries are required to power deep level <SPECIAL>mining<>operations. These highly durable sources can last for weeks, even in the extremes of heat and pressure found kilometres underground.

data.Name: OHMIC GEL
data.Subtitle: Tradable Energy Source
data.Description:
Several packets of ohmic gel.

Power-hungry <SPECIAL>mining<> operations are fraught with danger. Ohmic gel helps keep rapidly moving parts both insulated and lubricated.

data.Name: EXPERIMENTAL POWER FLUID
data.Subtitle: Tradable Energy Source
data.Description:
Corrosion-resistant barrels of an experimental power fluid.

One barrel of this highly volatile concoction is enough to power a space station for weeks on end. Particularly valued by <SPECIAL>mining<> economies.

data.Name: FUSION CORE
data.Subtitle: Tradable Energy Source
data.Description:
A slightly glowing bundle of fusion cores.

Power source, engine, high-capacity heater. A fusion core is the ultimate in deep-space power generation. Highly valued by <SPECIAL>mining<> economies looking to make their asteroid colonies more self-sufficient.

data.Name: DE-SCENTED PHEROMONE BOTTLE
data.Subtitle: Scientific Components
data.Description:
A loose collection of recycled pheromone bottles.

Vast quantities of pheromones are produced and distributed every day. This has spawned a lucrative <SPECIAL>trading<> opportunity for those willing to deal with the waste products. These glass jars have been thoroughly scrubbed and should pose no threat to the carrier.

data.Name: NEUTRON MICROSCOPE
data.Subtitle: Scientific Components
data.Description:
A parcel of neutron microscopes.

Scientific economies produce and consume large numbers of microscopes. However, some have slight defects that render them unsuitable for precision work. These are still a <SPECIAL>trading<> opportunity, in that they can be sold to those unable to tell the difference.

data.Name: INSTABILITY INJECTOR
data.Subtitle: Scientific Components
data.Description:
A jumbled box of instability injectors.

Grand experiments often require a large number of variables to be changed in a very short period of time. An instability injector provides such a service. They can also be used to create chaos in market systems; such unethical behaviour represents an excellent <SPECIAL>trading<> opportunity.

data.Name: ORGANIC PIPING
data.Subtitle: Scientific Components
data.Description:
A vat of preserved organic piping. Still warm.

To avoid difficult ethical problems, many labs grow their test subjects on a component level. The leftovers can be profitable in <SPECIAL>trading<> economies with relaxed medical regulations.

data.Name: NEURAL DUCT
data.Subtitle: Scientific Components
data.Description:
A box of fresh neural ducts.

Neural ducts are temporary inserts designed for a brief boost of concentration and productivity. Useful everywhere, these are highly valued in <SPECIAL>trading<> economies where competition between workers is fierce.

data.Name: DIRT
data.Subtitle: Tradable Minerals
data.Description:
Several tonnes of dirt.

Leftover dirt from mining operations. Residual metals can be extracted by specialists in <SPECIAL>manufacturing<> economies with the time and equipment to sift through it.

data.Name: UNREFINED PYRITE GREASE
data.Subtitle: Tradable Minerals
data.Description:
Large jars full of pyrite grease.

A fat solution with a high mineral content. This grease is highly valued by <SPECIAL>manufacturing<> economies, where it's used to keep large machinery oiled and glistening.

data.Name: BROMIDE SALT
data.Subtitle: Tradable Minerals
data.Description:
A crate of bromide salt.

The result of an extensive distillation and evaporation process, the bromide salt vats feed hungry factories in <SPECIAL>manufacturing<> systems.

data.Name: POLYCHROMATIC ZIRCONIUM
data.Subtitle: Tradable Minerals
data.Description:
A sack full of polychromatic zirconium crystals.

These crystals produce lenses of dazzling colour and near-indestructible hardness. Highly valuable in <SPECIAL>manufacturing<> economies.

data.Name: RE-LATTICED ARC CRYSTAL
data.Subtitle: Tradable Minerals
data.Description:
A neatly wrapped parcel of re-latticed arc crystals.

Extremely rare mineral formations, arc crystals are in high demand in <SPECIAL>manufacturing<> economies, where their hardness and conductivity is vital to several industrial processes. They also make alluring (if dangerous) jewellery.

data.Name: DECOMMISSIONED CIRCUIT BOARD
data.Subtitle: Technology Parts
data.Description:
A collection of salvaged circuitry.

<SPECIAL>Power generation<> economies go through vast numbers of high-tech components. As such, the demand is present even for highly damaged circuits, to be scavenged for parts or just plugged wholesale into low-quality power cores.

data.Name: WELDING SOAP
data.Subtitle: Technology Parts
data.Description:
Several large bars of welding soap.

Used in <SPECIAL>power generation<> systems to heat-clean metal diodes before they're fused into batteries.

data.Name: ION CAPACITOR
data.Subtitle: Technology Parts
data.Description:
A reinforced crate of ion capacitors.

These supercapacitors have an incredibly high energy density. In great demand in <SPECIAL>power generation<> economies.

data.Name: AUTONOMOUS POSITIONING UNIT
data.Subtitle: Technology Parts
data.Description:
A container of positioning units and associated wiring.

These APS units can be used to turn virtually any technology into a self-navigating system. Highly valuable in <SPECIAL>power generation<> economies, where they're used to remove conductive organic hands from the manufacturing process.

data.Name: QUANTUM ACCELERATOR
data.Subtitle: Technology Parts
data.Description:
Several large quantum accelerator units.
 
 Capable of propelling matter at unmeasurable speeds, these units are particularly important in <SPECIAL>power generation<> economies, where they're used to compress the energy stored in high-grade batteries.

data.Name: ATLAS STONE
data.Subtitle: Very high value curiosity
data.Description:
A spherical gem that seems to pulsate with red light from its centre.
 
An extremely rare item often associated with ancient monolithic sites.

data.Name: CAPTURED NANODE
data.Subtitle: Unique valuable curiosity
data.Description: Atlas Seed containing zonally-shifted quasi-stellar substrate. Warning: do not allow matrix to commune with this dimensional space.

data.Name: ENGLOBED SHADE
data.Subtitle: Unique valuable curiosity
data.Description: This Atlas Shell holds the remains of a parasitic space-borne lifeform, most likely of extra-dimensional origins.

data.Name: NOOSPHERIC ORB
data.Subtitle: Unique valuable curiosity
data.Description: An Atlas Seed capable of resonating on humanoid telepathic frequencies; may attempt to subsume any subordinate intellect in close proximity.

data.Name: DARK MATTER
data.Subtitle: Unique valuable curiosity
data.Description: An Atlas Seed shell encompassing a void element harvested from the collapse state of the last universe. Toxic if ingested.

data.Name: DAWN'S END
data.Subtitle: Unique valuable curiosity
data.Description: Sculpted tau neutrino-boson matrix fixed within an irreplaceable Atlas Seed shell. May be semi-sentient.

data.Name: PHOTIC JADE
data.Subtitle: Unique valuable curiosity
data.Description: This irreplaceable Atlas Seed is a form of matter-adapted photons coalesced into physical solidity by unknown means.

data.Name: STATE PHASURE
data.Subtitle: Unique valuable curiosity
data.Description: For unknown reasons, this unique Atlas Seed has been phased out of alignment with this quantum reality. Contents cannot be determined.

data.Name: NOVAE RECLAIMENT
data.Subtitle: Unique valuable curiosity
data.Description: Atlas Seed contains neutronium elements from a catastrophic supernova event that obliterated a sentient civilization in an earlier era.

data.Name: MODIFIED QUANTA
data.Subtitle: Unique valuable curiosity
data.Description: This one-of-a-kind Atlas Seed holds an aesthetically pleasing mathematical construct salvaged from the simulation of an alternate reality.

data.Name: HEART OF THE SUN
data.Subtitle: Unique valuable curiosity
data.Description: An Atlas Seed containing a time-locked quantum cilia suspended in a photonic shell. No others are known to exist.

data.Name: HEX CORE
data.Subtitle: Contained Reality Glitch
data.Description: This strange energy orb constantly vibrates, emitting a low-frequency drone. Slight variations in the pattern repeat over and over, almost as if it is attempting to relay a message.

data.Name: LARVAL CORE
data.Subtitle: Monstrosity
data.Description: A pulsating jellied orb, this gooey sphere is warm to the touch. Its stench triggers a primal fear in mortal beings, a deep-seated gnawing that begs you to drop it and flee.

data.Name: FUNGAL CLUSTER
data.Subtitle: Plantable Seed
data.Description:
A spherical fungus with internal gills, found only in toxic biomes. Fungal Clusters can be transplanted for cultivation, yielding a bountiful harvest.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Ensure Toxic climate before planting outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>30 mins<>

data.Name: FROSTWORT
data.Subtitle: Plantable Seed
data.Description:
A large crystal flower with radiant blue blooms, found only in snowy biomes. Frostwort can be farmed and makes a reliable crop, and its adaptation to harsh conditions results in highly frequent harvests.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Ensure Frozen climate before planting outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>15 mins<>

data.Name: GAMMA WEED
data.Subtitle: Plantable Seed
data.Description:
A luminous, leafy flowering plant that thrives in radioactive biomes and can be cultivated to yield a bountiful harvest.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Ensure Radioactive climate before planting outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>30 mins<>

data.Name: ECHINOCACTUS
data.Subtitle: Plantable Seed
data.Description:
Native to barren biomes and capable of withstanding long periods of drought, Echinocactus is an edible succulent that responds well to cultivation, yielding a large but occasional harvest.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Ensure Barren climate before planting outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>120 mins<>

data.Name: STAR BRAMBLE
data.Subtitle: Plantable Seed
data.Description:
A medium-sized, farmable plant that yields an occasional harvest of valuable Star Bulbs.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Ensure Lush climate before planting outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>30 mins<>

data.Name: SOLAR VINE
data.Subtitle: Plantable Seed
data.Description:
This 'living rock' is adapted to live in the extreme heat of scorched biomes. However, it can be farmed in most environments and, once established, yields a moderate harvest.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Ensure Hot climate before planting outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>120 mins<>

data.Name: MORDITE ROOT
data.Subtitle: Plantable Seed
data.Description:
An inedible tuber that produces a small yield of Mordite crystals.

A peaceful alternative to the process of harvesting Mordite from the <TECHNOLOGY>corpses of creatures<>. Mordite Root must be grown in a <TECHNOLOGY>Hydroponics Tray<>.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>60 mins<>

data.Name: COPRITE FLOWER
data.Subtitle: Plantable Seed
data.Description:
A foul-smelling, farmable flower that replicates the chemical structure of faecal matter. When planted inside, yields a harvest of Coprite.

A good alternative to collecting Coprite by hand, which requires <TECHNOLOGY>feeding creatures<> and then <TECHNOLOGY>harvesting their droppings<>. Coprite Flowers must be grown in a <TECHNOLOGY>Hydroponics Tray<>.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>30 mins<>

data.Name: GRAVITINO HOST
data.Subtitle: Plantable Seed

A strange, potentially parasitic plant that yields an occasional harvest of the highly tradable commodity, Gravitino Balls.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Cannot be planted outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>60 mins<>

data.Name: VENOM URCHIN

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Cannot be planted outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>40 mins<>

data.Name: ALBUMEN PEARL ORB

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Cannot be planted outdoors.

This medicinal herb is known for its pungent buds, which are harvested to produce Gek Nip. NipNip thrives in dank environments, and often grows as a weed.

Suitable for hydroponic planting indoors. Needs a tropical or humid climate before planting outdoors.

data.Name: Base Computer
data.Subtitle: Site Evaluation Device
data.Description:
Portable land registration service.

When placed, contacts Universal Cartographic Archive to establish ownership of land. Successful registration allows the construction of base modules across any site of the user's choosing.

data.Name: BASE TELEPORT MODULE
data.Subtitle: Long-Distance Matter Transfer Device
data.Description:
A <TECHNOLOGY>personal teleport device<>, allowing the user to move quickly between their constructed bases, as well as any Space Station Terminuses connected to their network.

User is urged to verify network integrity before inserting any matter they cannot afford to become separated from.

data.Name: BASE SALVAGE CAPSULE
data.Subtitle: Autonomous Storage Device
data.Description:
A <COMMODITY>construction recovery device<>.

This optional piece of base technology stores and preserves matter left over after the destruction of a previous base.

data.Name: FLEET COMMAND ROOM
data.Subtitle: Expedition Management Terminal
data.Description:
Core <TECHNOLOGY>Fleet Management Station<>. This advanced holographic communications station is vital for managing fleet expeditions from the comfort of your capital ship.

User is advised that multiple stations are required to manage more than one expedition at a time.

data.Name: BLUEPRINT ANALYSER
data.Subtitle: Technology Recovery Device
data.Description:
Portable <TECHNOLOGY>blueprint decryption device<>.

This field-deployable memory salvage module allows the user to recover valuable data from old or damage technology modules.

data.Name: PORTABLE REFINER
data.Subtitle: Automated Refinery Unit
data.Description:
A vital piece of planetary equipment. The <TECHNOLOGY>Refiner<> allows gathered substances to be processed into more powerful and more advanced materials.

The Portable Refiner can be <VAL_ON>dismantled and redeployed<> for easy transportation. Note: the Portable Refiner requires <FUEL>fuel<> to operate.

data.Name: MEDIUM REFINER
data.Subtitle: Automated Refinery Unit
data.Description:
A vital piece of planetary equipment. The <TECHNOLOGY>Refiner<> allows gathered substances to be processed into more powerful and more advanced materials.

The Medium Refiner allows <COMMODITY>two<> different substances to be combined into one new material, or materials to be processed at better ratios. 

The Medium Refiner must be installed in a <VAL_ON>Habitable Base<>, but does not require additional power sources.

data.Name: LARGE REFINER
data.Subtitle: Automated Refinery Unit
data.Description:
A vital piece of planetary equipment. The <TECHNOLOGY>Refiner<> allows gathered substances to be processed into more powerful and more advanced materials.

The Large Refiner allows <COMMODITY>three<> different substances to be combined into one new material, or materials to be processed at better ratios. 

The Large Refiner must be installed in a <VAL_ON>Habitable Base<>, but does not require additional power sources.

data.Name: OXYGEN HARVESTER
data.Subtitle: Atmosphere Processing Device
data.Description:
An <TECHNOLOGY>autonomous atmosphere extractor<>, this device can be left to collect and purify oxygen from the air. User must monitor fuel levels to ensure continued operation.

The resulting gas is compressed and processed, ready for use in all standard <FUEL>life support systems<>.

data.Name: APPEARANCE MODIFIER
data.Subtitle: Customise Personal Visuals
data.Description:
A buildable module that allows the users to <TECHNOLOGY>adjust their personal appearance<> settings.

The module applies advanced holographic techniques to recalibrate the light around the user, allowing them to adopt whatever appearance they desire. Visual data must be properly formated before use.
